<h2 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-Context/ProblemStatement">Con=
text / Problem Statement</h2>
<p>Our agentic platform serves as a foundation for building various AI agen=
ts. This platform handles requests, plans and orchestrates the agent and to=
ol selection along with execution. Currently multiple AI agents like SRE ag=
ent, Critic agent and Security agent are built on this platform that serves=
 different use cases and domains.</p>
<p>The platform enables agent orchestration and integration but lacks compr=
ehensive evaluation tools to assess the quality and effectiveness of the ag=
ent responses. We have resorted to manual evaluation to fill this gap. This=
 has resulted in quite a few challenges.<br><br><strong>Scalability concern=
s</strong> - Manual evaluations are tedious and resource intensive. This ap=
proach do not scale with increasing number of agents and use cases to solve=
. It also resulted in inconsistent evaluations based on who performed the e=
valuation.</p>
<p><strong>Lack of standardized evaluation methodology</strong> - There are=
 no consistent research backed methodologies or frameworks to assess the qu=
ality of the agent response. This would mean that different agents may have=
 varying response quality standards without common measurement unit.</p>
<p><strong>No historical performance data </strong>- Manual evaluations doe=
s not have numeric measure of quality thus making it impossible to analyze =
the response quality patterns over time.</p>
<h2 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-Design">Design</h2>
<p>Implement an automated evaluation system using <a class=3D"external-link=
" href=3D"https://github.com/confident-ai/deepeval" rel=3D"nofollow">DeepEv=
al</a> that uses LLM as a Judge technique to asses the agent response quali=
ty against a predefined criteria for each scenario. This system will integr=
ate with the agentic platform to provide batch evaluation capabilities. Thi=
s approach will result in a consistent and scalable assessment of response =
quality across all agents on the platform</p>
<h3 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-ArchitectureDiagram">Architec=
ture Diagram</h3><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-cent=
er-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedd=
ed-image image-center" alt=3D"AgenticEval Architecture.png" width=3D"468" l=
oading=3D"lazy" src=3D"41c9ea20da41ab2d10b801f412bed9661631e6e93077fed632ca=
98593012514e" data-image-src=3D"https://newrelic.atlassian.net/wiki/downloa=
d/attachments/4591125302/AgenticEval%20Architecture.png?version=3D1&amp;mod=
ificationDate=3D1756412848184&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-heigh=
t=3D"3659" data-width=3D"3840" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-lin=
ked-resource-id=3D"4592828425" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-link=
ed-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"Agent=
icEval Architecture.png" data-base-url=3D"https://newrelic.atlassian.net/wi=
ki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-co=
ntainer-id=3D"4591125302" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"12" dat=
a-media-id=3D"316693df-fcb5-4d5c-9b8d-36cf5d269326" data-media-type=3D"file=
" height=3D"446"></span>
<p></p>
<h3 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-Proposed/LeadingSolution">Pro=
posed / Leading Solution</h3>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-ImplementationDetails">Implem=
entation Details</h4>
<p>The proposed solution implements an evaluation engine that leverages Dee=
pEval framework to assess agent response quality via scheduled evaluation r=
uns. This approach transforms the current manual process into a repeatable =
data driven system that helps provides insights into the quality of agents.=
</p>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-DeepEvalFrameworkIntegration"=
>DeepEval Framework Integration</h4>
<p>The DeepEval serves as our underlying evaluation framework that orchestr=
ates and plans the evaluation flow. The framework support several state of =
the art metrics like G-Eval and RAG metrics( Answer Relevancy and Faithfuln=
ess ) that are becoming a standard for evaluating AI agents quality. The fr=
amework's G-Eval implementation uses LLM-as-a-judge methodology with chain-=
of-thought reasoning, providing human-like evaluation accuracy.</p>
<p>Integration with DeepEval allows for highly customizable evaluation crit=
eria that suits each agent=E2=80=99s specific requirements. For instance SR=
E agent might leverage DeepEval's <strong>G-Eval</strong> framework to defi=
ne custom evaluation criteria that assess incident response quality, techni=
cal accuracy of troubleshooting steps, and the actionability of recommended=
 solutions. While Security agent might focus on threat analysis using metri=
cs like <strong>Contextual Precision</strong> to verify that identified thr=
eats are genuinely present and not false positives, while <strong>Contextua=
l Recall</strong> ensures no critical security indicators are missed in the=
 assessment</p>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-ScheduledTestEngine">Schedule=
d Test Engine</h4>
<p>The Scheduled Test Engine is a lightweight orchestration engine that aut=
omates the execution of DeepEval tests for all the AI agents on the platfor=
m. The test engine runs periodically ( every hour as of now) and executes a=
ll the defined tests against the platform, evaluate the responses using Dee=
pEval and posts the results to New Relic as custom events. It is a long run=
ning background process that gracefully handles test execution failures and=
 continues with next scheduled execution.</p>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-ObservabilityandMonitoringStr=
ategy">Observability and Monitoring Strategy</h4>
<p>Results from each evaluations cycle are processed and formatted as custo=
m events for submission to New Relic. Each evaluation generate overall qual=
ity scores, reasoning for the score and execution metadata. This allows us =
to facet the metrics by different criteria to understand the the evaluation=
 scores. Historical data accumulation in New Relic supports trend analysis =
and helps identify gradual performance improvements or degradation. Teams c=
an also leverage New Relic alerts to be notified when evaluation scores dro=
p below the acceptable thresholds.</p>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-Exampleevaluation">Example ev=
aluation</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p>In this case we evaluate SRE agent response based on correctness metric =
( G-Eval )</p></li>
<li>
<p>We have chosen OpenAI as the LLM and config is passed as a pytest marker=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Prompt - Input to the agent (either by user or by automation such as ale=
rt destination)</p></li>
<li>
<p>actual_response - Actual response via execution of the deployed agent</p=
></li>
<li>
<p>expected_response - A desirable response from the agent</p></li>
<li>
<p>correctness_metric - Instructions for DeepEval on how to evaluate the ac=
tual response and the difference between actual and expected answers</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>Finally we capture the results and report them to New Relic as custom ev=
ent<br></p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">    @py=
test.mark.entity_lookup
    @pytest.mark.openai
    def test_entity_guid_lookup_alert_service(self, model_name, setup_agent=
ic_client):
        """Test SRE agent's ability to find Alert Service entity GUID"""
        question =3D "What is the entity guid for Alert Service - Productio=
n?"
        test_name =3D "test_entity_guid_lookup_alert_service"
        threshold =3D 0.7

        actual_response =3D setup_agentic_client.call_agent("sre_agent", qu=
estion)

        expected_response =3D "Entity GUID for Alert Service - Production i=
s: MTA5NDU4MTh8QVBNfEFQUExJQ0FUSU9OfDk4MTc2NDU4"

        correctness_metric =3D create_correctness_metric(
            criteria=3D"Does the response provide the correct entity GUID f=
or Alert Service - Production?",
            threshold=3Dthreshold,
            model_name=3Dmodel_name
        )

        test_case =3D create_test_case(
            input_query=3Dquestion,
            actual_output=3Dactual_response,
            expected_output=3Dexpected_response
        )

        results =3D evaluate([test_case], [correctness_metric])
        metric_data =3D results.test_results[0].metrics_data[0]

        event_data =3D {
            "score": metric_data.score,
            "reason": metric_data.reason,
            "success": metric_data.success,
            "metricName": metric_data.name,
            "testName": test_name,
            "inputQuery": question,
            "expectedResponse": expected_response,
            "actualResponse": actual_response,
            "threshold": threshold,
            "evalModel": model_name,
            "timestamp": int(time.time() * 1000)
        }

        send_custom_event_to_new_relic("AgenticTestResult", event_data)
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-OtherSolutionsConsidered">Oth=
er Solutions Considered</h4>
<h5 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-ArizeAIPhoenix">Arize AI Phoe=
nix</h5>
<p>Arize AI evaluates LLM applications through extensive observability into=
 LLM traces, but is extremely limited as it only offers three evaluation cr=
iteria: QA Correctness, Hallucination, and Toxicity.</p>
<p>Pros</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Strong observability and tracing capabilities.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Good for debugging and understanding LLM application behavior.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Cons</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Very limited evaluation metrics (only 3 criteria).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Insufficient coverage for comprehensive agent evaluation.</p></li>
</ul>
<h5 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-RAGAsFramework">RAGAs Framewo=
rk</h5>
<p>RAGAs was built specifically for RAG pipelines, offering 5 core metrics:=
 Faithfulness, Contextual Relevancy, Answer Relevancy, Contextual Recall, a=
nd Contextual Precision that make up the final RAGAs score. This framework =
focuses specifically on Retrieval Augmented Generation use cases.</p>
<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Purpose-built for RAG evaluation with proven metrics.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Incorporates latest research in RAG evaluation methodologies.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Limited to RAG specific evaluation, may not cover all agent types effect=
ively.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Less suitable for non-RAG agent evaluation scenarios.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-CostofGoodsSold(COGS)">Cost o=
f Goods Sold (COGS)</h3>
<h4 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-OperationalCosts:"><strong>Op=
erational Costs</strong>:</h4>
<p>Assuming 10 test scenarios per agent, running every hour using GPT 4.1 a=
s the model</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Average Cost for one LLM evaluation run: $0.015929 ( 1000 tokens * $0.00=
0015929)</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://staging.onenr.io/01wZKgNp4R6"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Average tokens</a> used per each call: ~500</p></li>
<li>
<p>We are making about 2 LLM calls per each evaluation</p></li>
<li>
<p>Average tokens for each LLM evaluation run: ~1000</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://staging.onenr.io/0vwB1lZKVQp"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Average Agentic Platform </a>cost for each request: ~ $0.=
50</p></li>
<li>
<p>Average cost for one evaluation run including platform cost: ~ $0.52</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>Monthly cost breakdown for one agent running in one env: $3715/month</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Evaluation cost: 10 test cases =C3=97 720 cycles =C3=97 $0.015929 =3D $1=
15/month</p></li>
<li>
<p>Platform cost: 10 test cases =C3=97 720 cycles =C3=97 $0.5 =3D $3600/mon=
th</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"EvaluatingAIAgentResponsesusingLLMs-Decision">Decision</h2>
<p><em>High-level summary of the discussion(s) that took place (when who wa=
s involved), what was discussed, and ultimately which solution was selected=
 as the best one to go forward with. If applicable, include the rationale/a=
rgument for the decision.</em></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
